    lgb_classifier =  lgb.LGBMClassifier(objective='multiclass',  metric='multi_logloss')

    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
   
    best_params = grid_search.best_params_
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_
    
    
    best_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    
    y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
    
    
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    

    
    return best_model, best_params, accuracy

def random_forest_custom_logic(X, y, test_size=0.2):

    params_grid = {
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'max_depth': [None, 5, 10, 20],

    y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
    
  
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    
    return best_model, best_params, accuracy

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

def random_forest_custom_logic(X, y, test_size=0.2):
    # Split data into train and test sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=test_size, random_state=42)
    
    
    params_grid = {
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'max_depth': [None, 5, 10, 20],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],
        'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4]
    }
    
   
    rf_classifier = RandomForestClassifier()
    
    
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=rf_classifier, param_grid=params_grid, cv=2, scoring='accuracy')
    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    
    best_params = grid_search.best_params_
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_
    
    
    best_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    
    y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
    
  
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    
    return best_model, best_params, accuracy

        'max_depth': [None, 5, 10, 20],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],
        'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4]
    }
    
    
    rf_classifier = RandomForestClassifier()
    
   
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=rf_classifier, param_grid=params_grid, cv=2, scoring='accuracy')
    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
   
    best_params = grid_search.best_params_
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_
    
    
    best_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
   
    y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
    
   
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    
    return best_model, best_params, accuracy

import lightgbm as lgb
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

def lightgbm_custom_logic(X, y, test_size=0.2):
    # Split data into train and test sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=test_size, random_state=42)
    
   
    params_grid = {
        'learning_rate': [0.01, 0.05, 0.1],
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'num_leaves': [20, 30, 40],
        'max_depth': [5, 7, 10]
    }
    
   
    X = balanced_df.drop(columns=['discount_analysis'])
    y = balanced_df.drop(columns=['discount_analysis'])
    
   
    lgb_classifier = lgb.LGBMClassifier(objective='binary', metric='binary_logloss')
    
   
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=lgb_classifier, param_grid=params_grid, cv=3, scoring='accuracy')
    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    
    best_params = grid_search.best_params_
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_
    
    
    best_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Predict on test data
    y_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)
    
    
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    

    
    return best_model, best_params, accuracy

import pandas as pd


# Function to generate unique class identifiers for each teacher
def generate_teacher_code(df):

    grouped = df.groupby('classteacher')
    

    teacher_codes = {}
    

    for teacher, group in grouped:
     
        teacher_code = "T" + str(hash(teacher) % 1000000)  
        
        teacher_codes[teacher] = teacher_code
        

    df['teacher_classid'] = df['classteacher'].map(teacher_codes)
    df= df.drop(['classid'],axis =1)
    return df


datax = generate_teacher_code(datax)

def recommend_classes_filter_time(df, teacher_name):
    similar_teachers = df[df['classteacher'] != teacher_name]['classteacher'].unique()
    recommended_classes = pd.concat([df[df['classteacher'] == teacher] for teacher in similar_teachers])
    # Filter by time (start between 3 PM and 6 PM)
    recommended_classes = recommended_classes[
        (recommended_classes['start_hour'] >= 15) & (recommended_classes['start_hour'] < 18)
    ]
    return recommended_classes
